snippet.textDisplay: good of you guys to encourage hand washing! but the 20 seconds thing is horribly inaccurate. The amount of time and scrubbing needed is a function of how much "stuff" there is on your hands to wash away. The lotion used in this video as demonstration is likely 1000x thicker than the layer of coronavirus particles likely to be on anyone's hand. This would be like you had lathered your hands in the mucus of an infected person. In that case, yes wash your hands like this. Otherwise, just a few seconds with soap and hot water is more than enough to wash the thin layer of microscopic viral particles off your hands
